General approaches, such as CG-MuAlign [Zhu2020] which employs Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) to perform multi-type entity alignment, leverages the neighborhood information and generalizes to unlabeled types, and REA [Pei20] which tackles the multi-lingual entity alignment problem by combining adversarial training with GNNs to cope with the problem of noisy labeled data provided as input.